<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <%- include("partials/head", { title }) %>
  <body>
    <div class="site">
      <%- include("partials/header") %>
      <main>
        <section class="section container">
          <article class="panel reveal" style="--delay: 0.1s;">
            <div class="section-header">
              <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
              <span class="section-line"></span>
            </div>

            <p class="note">Last updated: February 15, 2026</p>

            <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
            <p>
              This Privacy Policy explains how BFANG Team ("we", "our", "us") collects, uses, and
              protects information when you use our website and related services.
            </p>

            <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
            <p>We may collect the following categories of information:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Account details from OAuth providers, such as user ID, email address, display name, and avatar.</li>
              <li>Profile information you choose to provide, such as bio or social links.</li>
              <li>User-generated content, including comments and reading history.</li>
              <li>Technical and usage data needed for security, abuse prevention, and service reliability.</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>3. How We Use Information</h2>
            <p>We use collected information to:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Authenticate users and maintain account sessions.</li>
              <li>Provide website features (comments, profile, reading history, and moderation).</li>
              <li>Protect the platform from spam, abuse, and unauthorized access.</li>
              <li>Improve performance and user experience.</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>4. Google API Data</h2>
            <p>
              If you sign in with Google, we only request the minimum information required for authentication and
              account functionality. We do not sell Google user data.
            </p>
            <p>
              Our use and transfer of information received from Google APIs adheres to the
              <a class="inline-link" href="https://developers.google.com/terms/api-services-user-data-policy" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">
                Google API Services User Data Policy
              </a>, including the Limited Use requirements.
            </p>

            <h2>5. Sharing of Information</h2>
            <p>
              We do not sell personal information. We may share data only with trusted service providers necessary
              to operate the service (for example, hosting, database, and authentication providers), or when required
              by law.
            </p>

            <h2>6. Data Retention</h2>
            <p>
              We retain data for as long as needed to provide the service, maintain security and moderation records,
              and comply with legal obligations.
            </p>

            <h2>7. Security</h2>
            <p>
              We apply reasonable technical and organizational safeguards to protect data. However, no system can be
              guaranteed to be 100% secure.
            </p>

            <h2>8. Your Choices</h2>
            <p>
              You can stop using the service at any time, sign out of your account, and request profile updates or
              deletion where applicable.
            </p>

            <h2>9. Children's Privacy</h2>
            <p>
              Our services are not directed to children under the age required by applicable law in your jurisdiction.
            </p>

            <h2>10. Contact</h2>
            <p>
              For privacy-related questions, contact BFANG Team through our official website channels.
            </p>
          </article>
        </section>
      </main>
      <%- include("partials/footer") %>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
